<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Zoo Rescue Tracker</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #f1fff0;
      padding: 25px;
      padding-top: 70px;
      min-height: 1200px;
    }

    h1, h2 {
      color: #2d6a4f;
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .alert {
      position: fixed;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      right: 0;
      background: #2d6a4f;
      color: white;
      padding: 14px;
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .animal {
      background: #d8f3dc;
      border: 2px solid #2d6a4f;
      padding: 10px;
      margin: 8px 0;
      width: 220px;
    }

    .moved {
      position: relative;
      left: 35px;
      background: #95d5b2;
    }

    .card {
      position: relative;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid #52b788;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 25px;
      width: 230px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .tag {
      position: absolute;
      top: -10px;
      right: -10px;
      background: #f77f00;
      color: white;
      padding: 6px 10px;
      border-radius: 20px;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .zone {
      position: sticky;
      top: 50px;
      background: #2d6a4f;
      color: white;
      padding: 10px;
      margin-top: 25px;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .case {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid #52b788;
      padding: 10px;
      margin: 8px 0;
      width: 230px;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    code {
      background: #d8f3dc;
      color: #1b4332;
      padding: 2px 5px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <div class="alert">Zoo Rescue Alert - Emergency team active | Fixed</div>

  <h1>Zoo Rescue Tracker</h1>
  <p style="text-align:center;">Learn CSS positioning by placing animal cards, rescue tags, and sticky zone labels.</p>

  <h2>Static Positioning</h2>
  <p>Static is the default position. Animal entries appear one below another.</p>
  <div class="animal">Lion - Resting zone</div>
  <div class="animal">Elephant - Water zone</div>
  <div class="animal">Penguin - Ice zone</div>

  <h2>Relative Positioning</h2>
  <p>The rescued animal entry moves slightly using <code>left: 35px</code>.</p>
  <div class="animal">Giraffe - Checkup pending</div>
  <div class="animal moved">Rescued Koala - Safe</div>
  <div class="animal">Zebra - Feeding zone</div>

  <h2>Absolute Positioning</h2>
  <p>The rescue tag is placed on the animal card using absolute positioning.</p>
  <div class="card">
    Panda<br>
    Medical check complete
    <div class="tag">SAFE</div>
  </div>

  <h2>Fixed Positioning</h2>
  <p>The green rescue alert at the top stays fixed even when you scroll.</p>

  <h2>Sticky Positioning</h2>
  <p>The rescue zone label sticks near the top while scrolling.</p>

  <div class="zone">Rescue Zone Cases - Sticky</div>

  <div class="case">Tiger - Observation</div>
  <div class="case">Deer - Released</div>
  <div class="case">Owl - Night care</div>
  <div class="case">Turtle - Shell treatment</div>
  <div class="case">Rabbit - Healthy</div>
  <div class="case">Flamingo - Wing check</div>
  <div class="case">Monkey - Play area</div>
  <div class="case">Horse - Recovery stable</div>

  <h2>top, right, bottom, left</h2>
  <p>
    Use <code>top</code>, <code>right</code>, <code>bottom</code>, and <code>left</code>
    to control where positioned elements appear.
  </p>

</body>
</html>